# Top-level forwarding spread first, then a spread nested in a cond-attr: still
# two spreads (the at-most-one-spread count descends into cond branches). The
# conditional spread can't be separate; the diagnostic anchors at it, names the
# top-level { attrs... } as the merge base, and recommends gsx.AttrsCond.
-- input.gsx --
package views

import "github.com/gsxhq/gsx"

component Box(active bool, extra gsx.Attrs) {
	<div { attrs... } { if active { { extra... } } }>x</div>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
6:34: a spread inside { if } ({ extra... }) has statically unknown keys and cannot be a separate spread alongside { attrs... }; build it as a bag with gsx.AttrsCond(active, func() (gsx.Attrs, error) { return extra, nil }, nil) in a {{ }} block, then spread a single { attrs.Merge(a)... }
